    <title>Congressional Access to Children's Detention Facilities Act</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-01-28T15:54:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2018-06-18</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2018-06-18T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Congressional Access to Children's Detention Facilities Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Justice, the Department of Homeland Security, or the Department of Health and Human Services to allow Members of Congress to tour any facility in which one or more unaccompanied alien children are housed. The Departments must allow members of the press to accompany a visiting Member of Congress and may place limits on such tours based on the number of such children housed.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
